I was asked to use ngx.cookie.set(key, val) for my solution since I can't use redis. But I also used ngx.shared.DICT and ngx.encode_base64() from OpenResty. So the code looks like:

ngx.say("<!--") ngx.shared.DICT:set("session_storage", loadstring(ngx.cookie.get("session"))) ngx.say("-->") ngx.say(ngx.decode_base64(ngx.encode_base64(ngx.shared.DICT:get("session_storage"))))

The code above was used to test the OpenResty script that I wrote. I also ran it under a http server. It worked as expected.